title: Released from Nagpur jail after a decade, Saibaba says ‘it’s a miracle to be alive’
Sweden finally in Nato, ends decades of neutrality
description: Sweden officially became a member of Nato, marking a significant shift in its national security stance. This decision came two years after the invasion of Ukraine by Russia compelled Sweden to reassess its security policies, ultimately determining that aligning with the alliance was the most effective means to ensure the country's safety. Swedish Prime Minister Ulf Kristersson completed the final step of this prolonged process by submitting the necessary documentation to the US government, solidifying support from all Nato members for Sweden's inclusion in the military alliance.

title: MEA official in Afghanistan for trade talks with Taliban
description: India engages with Taliban leaders in Kabul, discussing humanitarian assistance, terrorism, drug trafficking, inclusive government, women's rights, economic cooperation, and education.

title: Colonel moves mountains, builds roads on China border
description: Colonel Ponung Doming, stationed at an altitude of 19,400 feet and facing -20 degrees Celsius in Hanle, Ladakh, serves as a pivotal figure in the army. In her role as the first female officer to lead the Border Roads Task Force (BRTF), the 42-year-old officer is actively supervising crucial road initiatives along the Line of Actual Control (LAC) with China. Colonel Doming is currently dedicated to overseeing the construction of 300 kilometers of roads in the Demchok sector, as well as managing the development of bridges and a fighter air base at Nyoma in eastern Ladakh.

title: BJP, TDP close to sealing deal on seats
Hijab-clad entrepreneurs break barriers, spark startup revolution
Rahul to fight in Wayanad, no decision yet on Amethi
description: Rahul Gandhi is poised to run for the Wayanad constituency after the Congress Election Committee gave its approval on Thursday for the candidacies of all 15 incumbent MPs from Kerala in the upcoming 2024 Lok Sabha elections. Among the 60 seats under consideration, the party has finalized names for 40. There are indications that the Congress will form an alliance with the CPM to contest in Tripura, with expectations that Tripura East will be contested by the alliance.

title: 18-yr-old cricket star sponsoring others to chase dreams with prize money & match fees
description: Putting on her pads, cricketer Soumya Tiwari would silently survey her surroundings, making a personal commitment that the moment she earned income from cricket, she would dedicate herself to assisting those unable to afford a bat or training. This pledge was made at the age of 11. Fast forward to the present, at 18, Soumya has emerged as a rising star in the cricket world and has stayed true to her word. Utilizing the prize money from her World T20 triumph and her match fees, the accomplished batting all-rounder is actively sponsoring aspiring cricketers hailing from underprivileged backgrounds.

title: Cong to wait for BJP list before deciding on Telangana candidates
description: The nominations of Kerala MPs were cleared based on the AICC screening committee's recommendation. The final decision lies with Rahul. K C Venugopal is a potential candidate from Alappuzha seat. The Delhi seats with multiple contenders were referred back to the screening committee. Telangana candidates have been partially cleared, pending observation of BJP candidates. The seat for Khammam remains undecided.

title: Women surpass men by 15% in drive to enrol new voters
description: In an ongoing nationwide voter registration campaign led by the Election Commission (EC) since January of the previous year, women have outpaced men in terms of new voter enrollments. According to the latest EC report, covering the 13-month period until January of the current year, women surpassed men by 15% in the addition of new voters. Out of the 2.6 crore individuals registered as new voters during this timeframe, 1.4 crore were women, while men accounted for 1.2 crore.

title: Modi shares selfie with ‘entrepreneur friend Nazim’
Govt extends LPG sop, announces 10k crore package for NE
Neutralisation of Art 370 has given azadi to Kashmiris: PM
description: During his first visit to Kashmir since the 2019 Article 370 nullification, Prime Minister Narendra Modi defended the decision, citing its positive impact on lives and accelerated development. Seeking an emotional connection with the people, he declared, "I have come to win hearts." Launching projects exceeding 6,000 crore at Srinagar's Bakshi stadium, Modi expressed dedication to winning the affection of Kashmiris, emphasizing his consistent efforts since 2014 to achieve this goal.

title: 820 crore ‘suspicious’ UCO Bank transfers draw CBI’s glare
NIA probes Bengaluru cafe blast suspect’s trail in Ballari
description: NIA investigators looking into the explosion at Rameshwaram Cafe on March 1 have discovered that the individual responsible for planting the bomb journeyed from Ballari, with indications suggesting a subsequent move to Pune. Although the specifics of his travel to the Maharashtra city remain unclear, it has been determined that on the night of March 1, he boarded a bus destined for Gokarna in Karnataka. To gather more information, NIA officials visited Ballari on Wednesday and reviewed CCTV footage from the New Bus Stand, revealing the suspect disembarking from one bus and boarding another.

title: Trade deal with 4 European nations before Lok Sabha elections
description: Commerce ministry will give the finishing touches to a trade deal with the European Free Trade Association — comprising Switzerland, Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein — after the Union cabinet is learnt to have approved the deal in-principle.  After holding back bilateral trade treaties for years, India has been on an FTA overdrive of sorts, signing agreements with Mauritius, Australia and the UAE, while holding talks with the UK, European Union, Oman and Sri Lanka.

title: Assets in her name doesn’t make wife accused in man’s DA case: HC
description: Orissa high court ruled that a man's wife cannot be accused of possessing disproportionate assets solely because assets are in her name. The court quashed the case against the wife in a corruption case due to lack of evidence and rejected the analogy of prosecuting every family member. She challenged the proceedings initiated against her for alleged abetment of the offence committed by her husband.

title: Yes, I want to make Aaditya CM: Uddhav after Amit Shah jibe
Isn’t Maha speaker decision contrary to our verdict: SC
description: On Thursday, the Supreme Court expressed an initial opinion that Maharashtra Speaker Rahul Narwekar's decision on January 10, acknowledging the Eknath Shinde faction as the authentic Shiv Sena due to its legislative majority, might potentially violate the court's May 2023 ruling. This ruling prohibited him from settling disputes solely based on the strength of group MLAs in the assembly. Chief Justice of India Chandrachud questioned, "Doesn't the speaker determine the genuine Sena party based on the legislative strength of the factions? Isn't this in contradiction to our judgment in the Subhash Desai case?"

title: DA crosses 50% of basic salary of government staff, allowances also up
CBI busts Russia jobs racket, search on in Delhi, Mumbai
‘Terminally ill have fundamental right to palliative care’
description: In 2018, following the creation of a passive euthanasia mechanism to provide a humane conclusion for individuals in a persistent vegetative state, the SC declared on Thursday that terminally-ill patients in this condition possess a fundamental right to palliative care until their natural demise. The Court requested a detailed report from the Centre regarding the implementation of such measures in government hospitals. During the presentation of the PIL, the petitioner, senior advocate Jayna Kothari, urged the SC to affirm that palliative care constitutes a component of the right to health under Article 21.

title: Hike carbon tax on imported fuel: Panel
Calling abrogation of Art 370 a black day no offence: SC
description: In a historic ruling, the Supreme Court declared on Thursday that the 'right to dissent lawfully' is integral to the right to life. The court stated that labeling the revocation of Jammu & Kashmir's special status under Article 370 as a "black day," along with expressing wishes for Pakistan's independence day, would not be considered an offense of promoting enmity between groups or communities on religious lines under Section 153A of the IPC.

title: Nod for AI mission with 10k-crore outlay for 5 years
Are there SOPs to help foreign tourists: HC to J'khand govt
PM Modi to launch 15 airport projects worth 10,000 crore
HC forms panel to probe protesting farmer’s death
description: The Punjab and Haryana high court established a committee led by a retired high court judge to probe the death of farmer Shubhkaran Singh. The incident occurred on February 21 during a clash between protesting farmers and Haryana police at the Haryana-Punjab border. Jaishree Thakur, a former judge of the High Court, will chair the committee, which will receive support from two ADGPs: Amitabh Dhillon from Haryana police and Pramod Ban from Punjab police. The high court noted that Punjab attempted to distance itself from the investigation into Shubhkaran's death.

title: Navlakha claims ‘extortion’ as NIA slaps Rs 1.6 cr security bill
description: Gautam Navlakha, one of the accused in the Bhima Koregaon case, has been under house arrest at Mumbai's Comrade BT Ranadive Memorial Library since November 2022, accompanied by Sahba Hussain. Authorities are demanding Rs 1.64 crore for escort protection charges, and Navlakha has only paid Rs 10.4 lakh of the amount. The NIA has contested a Bombay High Court order that granted bail to Navlakha in December of the previous year.

title: CCS gives go-ahead to indigenous 5th-gen stealth fighter project
description: India will develop its own fifth-generation stealth fighter, the AMCA, capable of achieving supersonic cruise speeds. The CCS approved the development of five AMCA prototypes and the procurement of 34 Dhruv helicopters. The first prototype will roll out in 4 years.

title: Employed women do 6 times more unpaid care work than males
description: Shifting attention to statistics revealing that employed Indian women engage in nearly six times more unpaid care work than their male counterparts, a recent strategy paper on the care economy underscores the imperative to reform leave policies, subsidize care services, develop infrastructure, and establish institutional mechanisms to address evolving challenges in light of India's changing demographic landscape. The paper estimates that the economic value of women's unpaid care and domestic work constitutes approximately 15%-17% of India's GDP, emphasizing the need for strategic interventions.

title: Every citizen has right to criticise abrogation of Art 370: SC
WPL: MI crush Warriorz by 42 runs to jump to second spot
description: Mumbai Indians extracted sweet revenge on UP Warriorz, defeating them by 42 runs to climb to the second spot in the standings of the Women's Premier League on Thursday. Opting to bat, MI overcame early jitters to post a decent 160/6. While Nat Sciver-Brunt (45 off 31) and skipper Harmanpreet Kaur (33 off 30) added 59 off 46 balls for the third wicket to steady MI's ship, the innings got impetus due to Amelia Kerr (39 not out off 23 balls) and rising star Sajeevan Sajana's (22 not out off 14 balls) knocks.

title: Former J&K deputy CM storms out of PM's rally over seating arrangements
description: Muzaffar Beig, a Padma awardee, left PM Modi's rally due to the lack of separate seating arrangements. Safeena Beig, the DDC chairperson, expressed disappointment and stated that they would take up the matter with the government. Other politicians, including Junaid Azim Mattu, Pervez Qadri, and Raja Ajaz Ali, also attended the rally.

title: Govt extends Rs 200 LPG subsidy for Ujjwala consumers till March 2024
description: The government has extended the Rs 300 subsidy on each LPG refill for another year. This subsidy benefits over 10 crore poor households who received free LPG connections through the Ujjwala scheme. The decision, approved by the Cabinet’s panel on economic affairs, will cost the government Rs 12,000 crore in the upcoming financial year.

title: Sweden officially joins Nato, ending decades of neutrality
description: Sweden officially joins Nato as the 32nd member, ending decades of neutrality. Concerns about Russian aggression in Europe following the 2022 invasion of Ukraine have prompted Sweden's decision. Swedish prime minister Ulf Kristersson visits the White House and attends US president Joe Biden's State of the Union address to Congress. Turkey and Hungary ratify Sweden's admission.

title: CBI busts human trafficking network taking Indians to Russia-Ukraine war zone
'The BJP babu ... ': Mamata slams ex-judge Abhijit Gangopadhyay
description: West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee criticized former Calcutta HC judge Abhijit Gangopadhyay for biased judgments and taking away jobs of youths. The chief minister also said that the “former judge” unnecessarily targeted the Trinamool. Abhishek Banerjee also said Gangopadhyay's move exposes the BJP's "twisted tango with a section of judiciary."

title: Microsoft-owned LinkedIn makes this ‘first-ever’ earnings disclosure
description: LinkedIn, owned by Microsoft, generated $1.7 billion in 2023 from its premium subscription service. The service offers AI tools for job seekers and users at $39.99/month. The number of premium subscribers increased by 25%. “Due to economic uncertainty individuals are taking steps to ensure they have the best possible opportunities to secure their desired jobs,” said Shapero.

title: 'Can't hide behind Bazball!': Hussain slams batting collapse
description: Spinners Kuldeep Yadav and R Ashwin grabbed nine wickets combined as India bowled out England for a lowly 218 inside 58 overs on the opening day of Dharamsala Test. India reached 135 for one at the close of play on Day 1, riding on openers' half-centuries. India lost Yashasvi Jaiswal for 57 late in the day as skipper Rohit Sharma and Shubman Gill walked back to the dressing room unbeaten on 52 and 26 respectively.

title: Cabinet approves 4% hike in DA for central govt employees
description: 7th Pay Commission: The Union Cabinet on Thursday approved a 4% hike in dearness allowance for central government employees, bringing the total to 50%. The hike in dearness allowance is determined by the central government based on the Consumer Price Index (CPI) data for industrial workers.

title: Congress holds CEC meet to declare candidates for 10 states for LS polls
description: The Congress party held discussions on the selection of candidates for the upcoming Lok Sabha polls in ten states. The Central Election Committee meeting discusses candidates for Uttar Pradesh, excluding Amethi and Rae Bareli. Smriti Irani criticizes the delay, suggesting a lack of confidence. Congress Working Committee to discuss the draft manifesto.

title: SC to hear 'Sena' dispute on April 8, Shinde's reply due by April 1
description: The Supreme Court has scheduled a hearing for the petition filed by Uddhav Thackeray's faction regarding the 'Sena vs Sena' dispute on April 8. Maharashtra Chief Minister Eknath Shinde's faction has been instructed by the court to submit a response to Uddhav Thackeray's group's plea by April 1. The court has called for all original records related to the disqualification of MLAs, including the Chief Minister, from the office of the Maharashtra Speaker.

title: Pak's Shehbaz Sharif replies to PM Modi's congratulatory message
description: Pakistan's newly elected PM Shehbaz Sharif thanked PM Narendra Modi for congratulating him on his re-election. PM Modi's curt message was in stark contrast to his congratulatory post in 2022, when Shehbaz had taken oath as PM for the first time, in which he had said India desired peace and stability in a region free of terror.

title: How Kuldeep 2.0 emerged as India's most impactful spinner
description: Despite facing challenging times, Kuldeep Yadav found little support around him when he needed it the most. The current captain, Rohit Sharma, has changed this narrative by providing the comforting support Kuldeep required. Notably, Kuldeep has experienced a resurgence in form across formats whenever Rohit has been at the helm.

title: Xiaomi launches its most-expensive smartphone ever in India
description: After unveiling the Xiaomi 14 series at MWC 24 for the global markets, Xiaomi’s new flagship phones—the Xiaomi 14 and Xiaomi 14 Ultra—have arrived in the Indian market. The Xiaomi 14 Ultra and Xiaomi 14 come with a Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 chipset on board and feature a Leica co-engineered triple camera setup. Here’s all that you need to know about the Xiaomi 14.

title: 'Stokes' aggressive captaincy reason behind England's...': Binny
description: BCCI president and former India seamer Roger Binny strongly feels that England skipper Ben Stokes' aggressive captaincy has been trumped by his Indian counterpart Rohit Sharma's patience and tactical nous in the ongoing series between the two teams. India have already clinched the five-Test series with an unassailable 3-1 lead and look good for a 4-1 final result after dismissing the visitors for 218 on the opening day of the fifth Test. India ended the day at a comfortable 135 for 1.

title: UPPSC PCS Prelims 2024 exam postponed, new schedule to be out soon
description: The UPPSC has delayed the UPPSC PCS 2024 preliminary exam to July 2024. Candidates should regularly check the official website for updates and to download their admit cards. The exam will consist of two papers, with Paper 1 counting towards merit ranking. It will be an offline exam with a two-hour duration.

title: 'Fake sandesh on Sandeshkhali': Mamata counters PM's attack
description: The West Bengal chief minister took on Prime Minister Narendra Modi, who had on Wednesday launched a broadside against the Trinamool government over the Sandeshkhali incident. Without naming the Prime Minister, the TMC supremo said, “Yesterday you came here and lectured us that atrocities on women are being committed here." "West Bengal is the safest state in the country for women," she said.

title: Why IT industry body sent mail to K'taka govt on Ola, Uber pricing
description: Nasscom and IAMAI urge Karnataka government to review uniform fare structure for cabs and taxis. Concerns raised over surge pricing, treating app-based taxi aggregators and non-app-based taxis equally, lack of industry-wide consultation, waiting charges for passengers, and need for restoration of dynamic pricing.

title: Calicut University Semester result 2024 out for UG, PG courses
description: The University of Calicut has announced the supplementary, Improvement, and regular results for various courses including BA, BSW, BCom, BBA, MVoc, and MSc. Students can view and download their UOC 2024 result by entering their register number on the official Calicut University website. Follow the provided steps or use the DIRECT LINK.

title: Apple Car dream: Why Steve Jobs' vision could never became a reality
description: It's been a week since the bombshell announcement that Apple had officially pulled the plug on its highly anticipated electric vehicle project. While Apple may have been over its car ambitions, the world around it isn’t. As the dust settles, new details continue to surface about the project's tumultuous history and ultimate demise.

title: My biggest hurdle in politics was fighting stereotypes: Shaina NC
Apple’s first foldable may also be its largest-screen device
description: Apple is reportedly working on a foldable MacBook with a 20.3-inch screen, aiming for a 2027 release. Analyst Ming-Chi Kuo suggests that Apple's plans for a foldable iPhone or iPad are still in the experimental phase.

title: How to update Aadhaar online, offline and more details
description: UIDAI advises Aadhaar cardholders to update their identity and address details on the myAadhaar portal using recent documents. Offline updates can be done by visiting Aadhaar centers. Rs 50 charge for document submissions. Download e-Aadhaar using enrollment number or Aadhaar number.

title: Best laptops under 50,000 to buy in March 2024
description: Want to buy the best laptops under 50000 online? We have a wholesome guide that will not only help you with the best choices but also a comparison of these laptops based on different features to help you make the right decision when you are buying a new laptop online.

title: 'Isko toh kuch bhi daal': Watch Rohit's viral stump-mic quip
description: India skipper Rohit Sharma came up with a hilarious one-liner on Jonny Bairstow during the fifth Test in Dharamsala, suggesting bowler Kuldeep Yadav, he can bowl anything to the batter. England folded for 218 in the final session on Day 1 with Kuldeep grabbing a fifer and Ashwin picking up four wickets.

title: Microsoft AI image generator has a 'sexualisation' problem
Why Mohammad Qasim Gujjar was declared designated terrorist by MHA
description: The Ministry of Home Affairs has designated Mohammad Qasim Gujjar, a member of Lashkar-e-Taiba (LeT), as a terrorist under the Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Act, 1967. Gujjar, associated with Hafiz Saeed's group, is currently in Pakistan Occupied Kashmir (POK). He has been actively involved in recruiting and radicalizing individuals through social media and encrypted communication apps, aiming to establish new terror networks.

title: 5th Test: Openers put India in charge after Kuldeep routs England
description: England's vulnerability against high-quality spin once again came to the fore before India demonstrated the art of batting on a flat track, effortlessly reaching 135 for one at stumps on day one of the fifth and final Test. Opting to bat, England found themselves struggling against the mastery of left-arm wrist spinner Kuldeep Yadav, who secured his fourth five-wicket haul in Tests. This allowed India to dismiss the visitors for 218 in their first innings shortly after tea.

title: 'Can disagree on many things, but ...': Jaishankar blames China for not observing written agreements
Watch: Kuldeep pays tribute to Ashwin with a touching gesture
description: The priceless camaraderie among players boosts team morale on the field, a sentiment evident during the initial day of the fifth Test against England in Dharamsala on Thursday.

title: UCO Bank Rs 820cr IMPS scam: CBI raids 67 locations in 7 cities
description: The CBI raided 67 locations in Rajasthan and Maharashtra, investigating an Rs 820 crore IMPS scam linked to UCO Bank. The probe focuses on 8,53,049 IMPS transactions that occurred between November 10 and November 13 last year. The raids took place in seven cities, as the central agency intensified its investigation. The official said searches in Rajasthan and Maharashtra.

title: Why RBI is targeting fintechs and shadow lenders
This may be Flipkart’s ‘Reliance plan’ to take on Blinkit, others
description: Walmart-owned Flipkart aims to enter India's hyper-grocery market, competing with BlinkIt, Instamart, Zepto, and BigBasket. It plans to launch an instant-delivery service in May, leveraging its supply chain infrastructure for same-day and next-day delivery options. Flipkart is also exploring to acquire Dunzo. Grocery delivery companies have also been working to cut down on the delivery times.

title: Jaiswal surpasses Kohli for most runs in Eng Test series
description: In the final session on the opening day of the fifth Test, Yashasvi Jaiswal went past Virat Kohli, who had previously scored 655 runs in the 2016 Test series at home. Yashasvi Jaiswal now holds the record for most runs scored by an Indian in a Test series against England.

title: Asia’s top 9 nature destinations: Ooty, Lombok, Hakone
description: Agoda and WWF launched a $1 million partnership for nature conservation in Southeast Asia. The program includes popular destinations like Ooty in India, Mount Rinjani-Lombok in Indonesia, Hakone in Japan, Miri in Malaysia, and Siquijor Island in the Philippines.

title: PM shares 'memorable selfie with friend' Nizam in Srinagar
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, during his first visit to Kashmir since the abrogation of Article 370 said that his government will continue working hard to win the hearts of people in the Valley.

title: Congress unveils youth-centric manifesto ahead of upcoming LS polls
description: Congress' 'Youth Manifesto' guarantees annual job package for diploma holders up to age 25, stringent laws against paper leaks, social security measures in gig economy, filling 30 lakh government job vacancies, fostering startups. Rahul Gandhi criticizes Modi and BJP for not filling government job vacancies.

title: Gold price today: Gold rate hits new high
description: Gold prices reached a new peak on the MCX, driven by expectations of a US Federal Reserve interest rate cut. Silver futures also saw an increase. The weakening dollar index and strong demand from China supported the surge. ET quoted Anuj Gupta from HDFC Securities. Neha Qureshi from Anand Rathi Commodities & Currencies analyzed the trend.

title: Rameshwaram cafe blast: Suspect 'bomber' travelled to Ballari after planting IED
description: NIA officials are investigating the Rameshwaram Café blast suspect who traveled to Ballari and then boarded a bus to Gokarna. CCTV footage shows the suspect avoiding camera surveillance on a BMTC's AC bus. The suspect's deboarding location is still unknown. According to sources, the suspect appears to have boarded the Mantralaya-Gokarna bus.

title: Kuldeep Yadav breaks the records of Axar and Bumrah
description: Kuldeep Yadav, the left-arm wrist-spinner, made his Test debut against Australia in 2017 at Dharamshala. He broke records by taking 50 Test wickets for India in 1871 deliveries.

title: Watch: B'luru cafe bomber spotted boarding a city bus
description: The recently released CCTV footage shows the alleged Rameshwaram Cafe bomber boarding a bus in Bangalore. NIA has announced a reward of Rs 10 lakh for information about the bomber. The blast occurred at the café in the Brookfield area.

title: At Srinagar rally, PM Modi announces his 'next mission'
description: PM Modi today promoted destination weddings in Indian locations like Jammu and Kashmir, highlighting the tourism boom after the G20 summit. While addressing a rally in Srinagar, PM Modi highlighted the success of the G20 summit held in Jammu and Kashmir, stating that the world is now witnessing a tourism boom in the region.

title: Watch: Gavaskar celebrates 10K Test runs anniversary in style
description: The Board of Control for Cricket in India celebrated Sunil Gavaskar's milestone of reaching 10,000 runs in Test cricket, making him the first batter to do so in the longest format of the game. Gavaskar cut a cake to commemorate the event and expressed gratitude to the BCCI for acknowledging the special moment.

title: PM Modi inaugurates 53 projects worth Rs 6,400cr in Kashmir
description: PM Narendra Modi visited Kashmir and inaugurated 53 developmental projects worth Rs 6,400 crores in agriculture and tourism after the abrogation of Article 370. The schemes include Dekho Apna Desh People's Choice Tourist Destination Poll, the Chalo India Global Diaspora Campaign, and the Holistic Agriculture Development Programme, which aims to train 2.5 lakh farmers, according to an official statement.

title: US court charges former Google engineer of stealing AI tech
description: Linwei Ding, former Google software engineer, charged with stealing trade secrets related to Google's AI technology while working for Chinese companies. He also held CTO roles at a start-up tech company and his own AI-focused company. In November 2023, he pitched his company at an investor conference. IT minister Rajeev Chandrasekhar shared a post, taking a dig at Chinese ‘innovation’.

title: Local BJP leader shot dead in UP's Jaunpur
description: A Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) leader, Pramod Kumar Yadav, was fatally shot by unidentified individuals in Sikrara. The incident occurred when Yadav was driving his car and was signaled to stop by motorcycle riders. Investigations are underway, and the culprits will be caught soon, according to the police.

title: Why Ashneer Grover wrote to RBI seeking probe into BharatPe
description: Ashneer Grover, the former managing director of BharatPe, has written to the Reserve Bank of India (RBI), alleging that the company intentionally deceived the regulator by adding a convicted fraudster to its shareholding.

title: Bengaluru's worst water crisis leaves IT capital high and dry
description: A coaching centre and a school in Bengaluru have asked their students to attend classes online due to an 'emergency' caused by an acute water crisis in Karnataka. The poor rainfall in 2023 has led to one of the worst water crises in recent years, with the Indian Meteorology Department attributing the scanty rains to the El Nino effect. Water tankers running frequently on the Bengaluru roads have become a common sight.

title: IndiGo's seat cushions missing: Flyer's social media post viral
description: A passenger raised concerns about missing seat cushions on an IndiGo flight. IndiGo explained that the cushions were removed for cleaning during departure, assuring passenger's safety. The incident gained attention with widely circulated pictures of cushion-less seats, raising concerns about cleanliness and hygiene.

title: Former Calcutta HC judge Abhijit Gangopadhyay joins BJP
description: Abhijit Gangopadhyay, who recently resigned as a judge in the Calcutta High Court, has joined the BJP. He expressed his happiness and stated his goal to remove the corrupt TMC regime from the state. Gangopadhyay's official joining was marked by a warm reception at the BJP office in Salt Lake, where he was handed the party flag by state party president Sukanta Majumdar.

title: 2 Tipra Motha leaders now ministers for BJP-led Tripura govt
description: Tripura's main opposition party Tipra Motha's senior leader, Animesh Debbarma, and MLA Brishaketu Debbarma took oath as ministers in the BJP-led government at Durbar Hall of the Raj Bhavan in Tripura, on Thursday.  This development comes days after the tripartite agreement which was signed between the Tipra Motha, the Tripura government, and the Centre in New Delhi on March 2.

title: 'My wife didn't know...': Ashwin delivers emotional speech
description: Ravichandran Ashwin was awarded his 100th Test cap by India's head coach Rahul Dravid during the fifth and final Test against England. Ashwin delivered a heartfelt speech, emphasizing the enduring value of Test cricket amidst the lucrative T20 leagues. He emphasized that the IPL has been a popular tournament, and many people want to play T20 to get into the IPL.

title: How Pakistan's Seema Haider may hv added to BGMI's India troubles
Watch: Gill's excellent catch to dismiss Duckett in 5th Test
description: Frustrated after playing far too many dot balls by his standards, Duckett (27) went for a massive whack on the leg-side, but the googly went low and skewed a thick top-edge into the air on the off-side where Gill, ran sideways to his right from cover and put in a splendid well-timed dive to grab the catch.

title: Electoral bonds disclosure: Contempt plea in SC against SBI
description: An NGO filed a contempt plea in the Supreme Court against SBI's move to seek extension for disclosing details of electoral bonds encashed by political parties. SBI missed the SC deadline for information disclosure, potentially keeping political funding secret till Lok Sabha polls end.

title: Microsoft engineer to FTC: Company 'refused' to take down Copilot designer
Ashwin joins 100-Test club, receives tribute from Dravid
description: Ravichandran Ashwin on Thursday became the 14th Indian player to feature in 100 Test matches. He achieved this during the fifth Test against England at the Himachal Pradesh Cricket Association stadium in Dharamsala. India's head coach, Rahul Dravid, commemorated Ashwin's 100th Test match by presenting him with a special memento.

title: 'Wonder Woman' star Gal Gadot welcomes baby girl 'Ori'
description: Gal Gadot welcomed her fourth daughter, Ori, expressing gratitude despite pregnancy difficulties. Her family now consists of five girls. Known for her role as Wonder Woman, Gadot recently starred in Netflix's 'Heart of Stone' and advocates for equality and social justice.

title: 7-yr-old raped, axed and strangled to death in MP's Chhindwara
description: A 7-year-old girl was raped, axed, and strangled to death in Chhindwara district of Madhya Pradesh. The accused buried her body and fled the spot. Sonu Pandram, a relative of the victim, confessed to the crime and guided the police to the burial site in Junnardev. He has been charged with rape and murder.

title: Navy comes to the rescue of missile hit ship in Gulf of Aden
description: The Barbados-flagged Bulk Carrier MV True Confidence was hit by a drone or missile approximately 55 nautical miles southwest of Aden, sparking a fire onboard and causing critical injuries to several crew members. In response, INS Kolkata arrived at the scene and successfully rescued 21 crew members, including one Indian national, from life rafts using its integral helicopter and boats.

title: Punjab police arrests 2 members of Babbar Khalsa-backed module
description: The Punjab Police has successfully thwarted potential target killings by apprehending two individuals associated with the Babbar Khalsa International-backed terror group. The mastermind, Harpreet Singh, also known as Happy Passian, is a close aide of terrorist Harwinder Singh, alias Rinda, based in Pakistan. Another member, Shamsher Singh, known as Shera, is residing in Armenia. They were involved in radicalizing youth and promoting anti-national activities in Punjab. The police seized two pistols, four magazines, and 30 live cartridges, and a case has been filed against them under UAPA and Arms Act.

title: Navy commissions first MH60R Seahawk chopper squadron
description: The Indian Navy has commissioned the country's first MH60R Seahawk multirole helicopter squadron during a ceremony at INS Garuda in Kochi on Wednesday. The squadron has been commissioned as Indian Naval Air Squadron (INAS) 334 Seahawks. Six MH 60R helicopters with the Navy, which are part of a 24-aircraft contract signed with the US govt in Feb 2020, will be part of the Navy's latest air squadron.

title: Sumit Nagal replaces Rafa Nadal at Indian Wells main draw
description: Rafael Nadal has withdrawn from the 2024 Paribas Open due to his lack of readiness to compete at the highest level. Nadal expressed regret over his inability to participate in the prestigious tournament despite being on-site in the California desert and engaging in training sessions. He will now be replaced by Sumit Nagal of India, a lucky loser from India.

title: SBI misses deadline for electoral bond declaration
description: SBI missed the deadline to disclose electoral bond details. They requested an extension until June 30th. The Chief Justice-led bench declared the bonds unconstitutional, instructing SBI to reveal each bond's date and denomination. Election Commission to publish information on SBI website by March 13th.

title: Padikkal fifth Indian to make Test debut in England series
description: Batter Devdutt Padikkal got his maiden India Test cap in the final match against England in Dharamsala, replacing injured Rajat Patidar. Padikkal's debut marks the fifth debut for India in the series. However, England captain Ben Stokes chose to bat first after winning the toss, preventing Padikkal from showcasing his skills.

title: Remember Bilkis Bano? TMC hits back at PM Modi's speech
description: TMC criticizes BJP for shielding criminals and rapists, questions their record on women's safety and empowerment, and highlights Bengal's model. They urge BJP to learn from Bengal's success and improve their own record on women's rights.

title: RBI on Paytm: Driving Ferrari does not mean you disobey traffic rules
description: RBI governor Shaktikanta Das reiterated that the bank has nothing against the Fintech sector. Action against Paytm Payments Bank was due to non-compliance. The deadline for linking the wallet attached with PPBL with other banks is March 15.

title: BJP worker hacked to death by Maoists; ninth in Bastar
description: The murder of Kailash Nag, a BJP worker, by Maoists in Bijapur district highlights the ongoing violence against BJP leaders in the region. This is the latest in a series of targeted attacks that have claimed the lives of several party members.

title: 'Where will you go - BJP or jail?': Kejriwal's dig at Tapas Roy
description: Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal accused former TMC leader Tapas Roy, who just joined the BJP after the ED raided his home, of exploiting the ED to harass ministers. This is the truth of ED and Modi government. How people are included in BJP by getting harassed by ED," he said.

title: 'Incredible cricketer, no doubt about it': Ponting praises Ashwin
description: Ricky Ponting has praised Indian spin maestro Ravichandran Ashwin for his exceptional skills and dedication. Ashwin, who has taken 507 wickets in 99 Tests at an average of 23.91, including 35 five-wicket hauls, makes his 100th Test appearance in the 5th India-England Test in Dharamsala. Ponting praised Ashwin's mastery of spin bowling across various conditions, highlighting his exceptional career.

title: Sundar Pichai on how AI will empower people to achieve more
description: At the HP Amplify conference, Sundar Pichai discussed Google's AI efforts, emphasizing its potential for fostering human creativity and productivity. He also highlighted the rapid pace of AI innovation.

title: Anderson completes half-century of Test venues in Dharamsala
description: England's James Anderson achieved a significant milestone as the fifth and final Test match against India takes place in Dharamsala. The England Cricket Board announced that Dharamsala is the 50th ground Anderson has played Test cricket at, underlining the significance of his journey across the cricketing globe.

title: Dr Hansaji Yogendra shares how to stay active and energetic at 76
description: Dr. Hansaji Yogendra, a 76-year-old yoga expert, shares her secrets to staying energetic and happy. Yoga calms the mind, blends psychology and philosophy, and emphasizes the importance of inner peace. Age is just a number when it comes to experiencing the transformative power of yoga.

title: Sandeshkhali women apprise PM Modi of sexual ordeal
description: Modi met five women accusing Shahjahan of sexual harassment and intimidation. Late women agitated, demanding to meet Modi. Bengal BJP will send testimonials to PMO. Women said Modi listened like a family guardian and sought justice.

title: JEE Main Paper 2 result 2024 out
description: The National Testing Agency (NTA) has released the results for the JEE Main Paper 2 (B.Arch & B.Plan) exam held in January 2024. Candidates can now view their percentile scores and All India Rank (AIR) on the official website. These scores are vital for admission to architecture and planning programs across India. Students should carefully review and download their scorecards. The next session of JEE Main is scheduled for April 2024, with ongoing registrations.

title: Man-wildlife conflicts now a state-specific disaster in Kerala
description: The cabinet declared human-wildlife conflicts as a state-specific disaster and set up committees to address the issue. Remedial measures include social media groups, temporary forest watchers, communication equipment, water sources, inter-state coordination, guidelines for eliminating wild boars, and KIIFB fund allocation.

title: Hyderabad man's dream of living abroad ends in Russia: Who was Mohammed Afsan
description: Mohammed Afsan, a man from Hyderabad, was duped into joining the Russian army and was killed in the war with Ukraine. His family seeks proof of his death and demands prompt action from the Indian government.

title: Rs 500 crore tax evasion: Evidence found hidden in Rajkot slum
description: The income tax department in India uncovered incriminating data related to alleged tax evasion by the Ladani Group. Ankit Shira and Raj Sisodia were found to be handling the black money transactions. The data was stored in laptops and physical files hidden in a slum room.

title: Telangana reservoirs drying up, brace for drought: CM Reddy
description: Chief Minister A Revanth Reddy expressed concern over the depleting water levels in reservoirs and called on farmers to cooperate with the government to overcome the water scarcity problem. He also announced his campaign against PM Modi if he doesn't support Telangana's development.

title: Court summons Kejriwal after fresh complaint by ED
description: ED files application against Arvind Kejriwal for avoiding summonses related to Delhi liquor scam. Court proceedings ongoing. AAP criticizes ED's summonses, accuses Central govt of disregarding court orders.

title: Ex-Kerala CM's daughter Padmaja Venugopal joining BJP?
From hero to zero: Rajasthan SI exam ‘topper’ suffers fall
description: Naresh Kumar, adorned with garlands, secured top spot in the sub-inspector exam after jubilant celebrations. He is arrested by SOG for fraudulently obtaining question paper and using a dummy candidate. Trainee sub-inspectors were detained for using unfair means. SIT prevents paper leaks.
